criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Have been referred for pulmonary rehabilitation for chronic obstructive pulmonary
             disease diagnosis;

          -  Stable for the last 3 months and have no contraindications to exercise (no infection,
             acute myocardial infarction, malignant neoplasms, renal or hepatic disease, ascites /
             edema or neuromuscular disease);

          -  Be 40 years or older;

          -  Being literate;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Being a vegetarian;

          -  Make use of continuous oxygen;

          -  Present cognitive or functional changes that limit the execution of any of the
             proposed tests.

          -  Body mass index <21.0 kg / m² and ≥ 35.0 kg / m².
